==English==

===Adjective===
'''sketchy'''
#roughly or hastily laid out; intended for later refinement
#:''The first draft included a sketchy design.''
#of questionable or doubtful quality
#:''The sketchy repair job did not look like it would hold.''
#(''of a person'') suspected of taking part in shady dealings
#:''That guy at the bar has staring at us for ten minutes.  He's sketchy.''
#pertaining or related to actions committed in the style of Giovannino Guiseppe Gazzola
#:''That guy's salute is all sketchy.''

